## 5. Feature Description

### 5.1 User Authentication & Profiles

* User registration, login, logout
* Profile creation with bio, profile picture, cover photo
* Privacy settings (public / private profiles)

### 5.2 Posts

* Create, edit, delete posts
* Upload images with posts
* Post timestamps and ordering

### 5.3 Likes & Comments

* Like and unlike posts
* Comment on posts
* Dynamic count of likes and comments

### 5.4 Friend & Following System

* Send and receive friend requests
* Accept or reject requests
* Follow and unfollow users
* Friend suggestions

### 5.5 Notifications

* Notifications for likes, comments, follows
* Real-time updates using WebSockets
* Mark notifications as read

### 5.6 Search & Filtering

* Search users by username
* Search posts by content
* Filter posts by date or author

### 5.7 Privacy & Content Moderation

* Private profiles visibility control
* Flag inappropriate posts
* Admin moderation via Django Admin

### 5.8 REST API

* API endpoints for:

  * Users
  * Posts
  * Comments
  * Friends
  * Notifications
* Token-based authentication
* Swagger API documentation


## 6. API Documentation

### API Base URL

```
/api/
```

### Sample Endpoints

* `GET /api/posts/`
* `POST /api/posts/`
* `POST /api/posts/{id}/like/`
* `POST /api/posts/{id}/comment/`
* `GET /api/notifications/`

Swagger UI available at:

```
/swagger/
```


## 7. Database Design

### Key Models

* User (Django default)
* UserProfile
* Post
* Comment
* FriendRequest
* Notification

### Relationships

* One-to-One: User → UserProfile
* One-to-Many: User → Posts
* Many-to-Many: Likes, Friends


## 8. Security Considerations

* Django authentication & authorization
* CSRF protection
* Password hashing
* Environment variables for secrets
* Access control for private content


## 9. Testing

### Testing Strategy

* Unit tests for models
* View tests for authentication and permissions
* API tests using DRF test tools

### Test Coverage

* User registration & login
* Post creation and interactions
* Friend request logic
* Privacy enforcement


## 10. Deployment Guide

### Deployment Steps (Render)

1. Push code to GitHub
2. Create new web service on Render
3. Set environment variables
4. Configure database
5. Run migrations
6. Collect static files
7. Deploy application

### Environment Variables

```
SECRET_KEY=
DEBUG=False
DATABASE_URL=
ALLOWED_HOSTS=
```


## 11. Future Enhancements

* Real-time chat system
* Groups and communities
* Events and RSVPs
* Advanced analytics dashboard
* Mobile application integration


## 12. Conclusion

This project demonstrates a **complete, production-ready social media platform** built using Django. It covers authentication, social interaction, APIs, real-time features, and deployment, making it suitable for academic submission, portfolio presentation, and real-world use.


